getFile

java.io.File getFile()
Return the path to a File containing the contents of this MIME resource. The file may or may not be the actual path from which the MIME resource was loaded. This is provided merely to support clients who, in order to comply with some legacy API, must obtain their data from a File. New code is *very* strongly discouraged from deliberately relying on this feature.

Returns:
a File from which the contents of this MIME resource may be read.
